# File Structure

- Server Components are the default. Mark Client Components with `'use client'` at the top of the file — and only when interactivity is truly needed.
- Server Actions live in `actions.ts` **adjacent to the route that uses them**. Start the file with `'use server'`.
- One exported action per function, named camelCase with a verb.
- Validation schemas are colocated with actions, named `XxxxSchema`, using Zod.
- Shared components go in `components/`; route‑local components stay in the route folder.
- Utilities in `lib/` are grouped by domain: `lib/fx/`, `lib/supabase/`, `lib/format/`, ...
- Supabase types are generated into `supabase/types.ts`. Import as `Database['public']['Tables']['xxx']['Row']`.

## Supabase client split

- `lib/supabase/server.ts` — Server Components & Actions (uses cookies)
- `lib/supabase/client.ts` — Client Components
- `lib/supabase/middleware.ts` — auth refresh in middleware
- **Never** import the server and client variants from the same file.

# Naming

| Kind | Style | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Files | kebab-case.ts | `money-input.tsx`, `create-transaction.ts` |
| Components | PascalCase | `MoneyInput`, `TransactionRow` |
| Functions | camelCase | `formatAmount`, `createTransaction` |
| Types / Interfaces | PascalCase | `Transaction`, `CreateTransactionInput` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE | `BAM_EUR_RATE`, `MAX_PDF_SIZE` |
| DB columns | snake_case | PostgreSQL convention; transform at the boundary |
| Routes | Bosnian kebab-case | `/transakcije`, `/racuni/[id]`, `/uvoz` |
